race.comment: BLINDING LUCK (9) will find this easier than her debut campaign. She's trialled nicely at this course recently where she showed good speed to lead throughout. Needs a touch of luck from out wide, but carries no weight for the leading jockey. Can resume on a winning note. SIZE MATTERS (3) will be fitter for the fresh effort where he was a little slow to begin. He gets the blinkers on now and should be fitter for the fresh effort. The rise in trip is also a big bonus for him and an improved run is on the cards. MA DAME (11) is on debut for the Steve Wolfe barn and creates plenty of interest. Her latest trial was very good behind Binding Luck and she maps for a lovely run in transit. Can make an impact. MENOMONEE BRAVE (7) is another who comes through the trial behind Binding Luck and that looks a key form indicator for this event. BAGGER PRINCE (2) is next best.
